A Catholic Priest, Rev Fr Joseph Shekari, has been abducted by suspected terrorists in Chawai, a community in the Kauru Local Government Area of Kaduna State.  During the attack, his cook was reportedly killed. Suspected terrorists have abducted a Catholic Priest, Rev Fr Joseph Shekari, in Chawai, a community in the Kauru Local Government Area of Kaduna State and also killed his cook during the attack. According to reports, the assailants stormed the parish house at about 11.30pm on Sunday, February 6. They allegedly fired gunshots killing the cook before whisking the clergyman to an unknown destination. The assailants are yet to make any contact with the parish house or the family of the abducted clergyman.  source By Chukwuemeka Opara Abakaliki -  The Ebonyi Police Command has rescued a Catholic priest, Rev. Fr. Timothy Nwanja, abducted by gunmen in Okpokueze Nkomoro community, Imoha Development Centre of Ezza North Local Government Area. The News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) reports that the priest, who serves at St. Mary’s Parish… In "News" According to a Sunday Punch report, the Catholic Diocese of Enugu on Saturday confirmed the attack on Rev. Fr. Ikechukwu Ilo by Fulani herdsmen along Numeh- Nenwe road in the Nkanu East Local Government Area of Enugu State. There was palpable tension in Numeh and neighbouring communities in Nkanu East… In "News" By Stanley Nwanosike Enugu - The Enugu State Police Command has launched a manhunt for the abductors of  the traditional ruler of Obom, Agbogugu Community in the Awgu Local Government Area of the state. Igwe Sunday Orji was abducted on Aug. 1, in the latest high-profile crime in Enugu State,… In "Metro"